{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BB43QR4fSu2BcnNtnKw3MH","type":"tool_result","content":"8-  - architecture-multi-framework.md (TUI component architecture)\n9-workflowType: 'ux-design'\n10:note: 'Multi-lane TUI UX for parallel epic execution, merge status, and telemetry visibility'\n11----\n12-\n--\n22-**New UX surfaces:**\n23-1. Multi-lane TUI rendering during `codeharness run --live`\n24:2. Merge status and conflict resolution display\n25:3. Lane lifecycle visualization (create → execute → merge → cleanup)\n26-4. Telemetry visibility (optional, not in default view)\n27-5. Updated `codeharness status` for parallel runs\n--\n32-\n33-9. **Lanes are independent.** Each lane is self-contained — a failure in lane 1 doesn't pollute lane 2's display.\n34:10. **Merge is a first-class event.** Merge attempts, conflicts, resolutions, and test results are visible — not hidden in logs.\n35-11. **Parallel ≠ noisy.** Two lanes should be as readable as one lane was. Compress, don't duplicate.\n36-\n--\n62-- Each lane shows: epic title, current story + phase + AC progress, story progress bar, driver + cost/time\n63-\n64:**Summary bar:** Between lanes and activity. Shows: done count, merge status, pending epics.\n65-\n66-**Activity section:** Shows the MOST RECENTLY ACTIVE lane's tool/thought/retry. Only one activity stream at a time — the one that last produced output. Prefixed with lane number.\n--\n105-### Merge In Progress\n106-\n107:When an epic completes and merges:\n108-\n109-```\n--\n116-\n117-```\n118:[OK] Merge epic-14 → main: clean (0 conflicts)\n119-[OK] Tests: 1650/1650 passed (18s)\n120-[OK] Worktree cleaned: /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-14\n--\n125-\n126-```\n127:[WARN] Merge epic-11 → main: 1 conflict in src/lib/workflow-engine.ts\n128:[INFO] Dispatching merge agent...\n129-```\n130-\n--\n132-\n133-```\n134:Done: ... │ Merging: epic-11 → main (resolving 1 conflict) ◌ │ Pending: ...\n135-```\n136-\n--\n138-\n139-```\n140:[OK] Merge epic-11 → main: 1 conflict auto-resolved\n141-     └ src/lib/workflow-engine.ts: additive changes in different functions\n142-[OK] Tests: 1652/1652 passed (19s)\n--\n147-\n148-```\n149:[FAIL] Merge epic-11 → main: conflict unresolvable after 3 attempts\n150:       └ src/lib/workflow-engine.ts: semantic conflict in dispatchTaskWithResult()\n151-       └ Epic 10 refactored function signature, epic 11 added parameters\n152:       → Manual resolution required\n153-       → Worktree preserved: /tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-11\n154-       → Branch: codeharness/epic-11-workflow-schema\n--\n158-### Cross-Worktree Test Validation\n159-\n160:After merge, before cleanup:\n161-\n162-```\n163:[INFO] Running cross-worktree test validation on merged result...\n164-[OK] Tests: 1652/1652 passed (19s)\n165-[OK] Coverage: 96.8% (target: 90%)\n166-```\n167-\n168:If tests fail after merge:\n169-\n170-```\n171:[FAIL] Cross-worktree test validation failed after merge\n172-       └ 3 tests failed in src/lib/workflow-engine.test.ts\n173:       └ Merge conflict resolution may have introduced regression\n174:       → Reverting merge: git reset --hard HEAD~1\n175:       → Dispatching merge agent with test failure context (attempt 2/3)\n176-```\n177-\n--\n270-| Lane number | cyan | Active lane indicator |\n271-| Merge in progress | yellow | Merging status |\n272:| Merge clean | green | Successful merge |\n273:| Merge conflict | red | Conflict detected |\n274-| Merge resolved | green | Auto-resolved |\n275-| Merge escalated | red bold | Manual intervention needed |\n276:| Test pass (post-merge) | green | Cross-worktree validation |\n277:| Test fail (post-merge) | red bold | Regression detected |\n278-| Worktree active | dim cyan | Active worktree path |\n279-| Worktree cleaned | dim | Cleaned worktree |\n--\n301-  <SummaryBar />                # NEW: done, merging, pending\n302-  <Separator />\n303:  <MergeStatus />               # NEW: merge progress, conflicts, test results\n304-  <ActivityDisplay />           # Existing: shows most recently active lane\n305-</App>\n--\n320-### `Ctrl+M` — Toggle Merge Detail\n321-\n322:When a merge is in progress, `Ctrl+M` expands/collapses merge detail in the merge status section. Default: collapsed (one-line summary). Expanded: full conflict list, agent output, test results."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01WnnpXgRY1Zao1mENPUGorH","session_id":"74f4684f-cc80-4828-8405-943cba326449","uuid":"6820998c-1ed9-4a74-a170-f11cd8d1ae42","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:41:49.756Z"}
