{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011KW5B7oWpj1MKDHqa2H54S","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## Summary\n\nImplemented Story 18-2: Merge Agent for Conflict Resolution. All 5 tasks complete, all 10 acceptance criteria addressed.\n\n### Files created\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/merge-agent.ts` — New module (~210 lines) with `MergeConflictContext` and `ConflictResolutionResult` interfaces, `buildConflictPrompt()`, `resolveConflicts()` with 3-attempt retry loop, test suite runner, and escalation logic.\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/merge-agent.test.ts` — 23 unit tests covering all acceptance criteria.\n\n### Files modified\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` — Added `OnConflictCallback` type, `onConflict` optional parameter to `mergeWorktree()`, and conflict callback invocation logic. When callback returns `resolved: true`, cleanup proceeds. When `escalated: true`, merge is aborted and conflict result returned. No callback = existing behavior.\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/worktree-manager.test.ts` — Added 5 tests for onConflict callback behavior.\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/18-2-merge-agent-conflict-resolution.md` — Status set to `review`, all tasks checked.\n\n### Test results\n- merge-agent: 23/23 passed, 100% line coverage\n- worktree-manager: 66/66 passed (including 5 new onConflict tests)\n- No TypeScript errors in modified files\n- No regressions\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- The `onConflict` callback in `mergeWorktree()` passes `driver: undefined as never` in the `MergeConflictContext` because the `WorktreeManager` does not hold a driver reference. The story spec says the caller (lane pool) is responsible for providing the driver, but the type signature means the callback receives a broken `driver` field. The caller must override/wrap this. This matches the spec (\"This story adds the callback parameter; callers are wired later\") but is a known gap.\n- The `mainDescription` and `branchDescription` fields are passed as empty strings from `mergeWorktree` — the WorktreeManager has no knowledge of epic descriptions. The caller must construct the full `MergeConflictContext` when wiring the callback in Epic 19.\n- Pre-existing TypeScript errors in other files (run.test.ts, issue.ts, workflow-engine.test.ts, etc.) — not introduced by this story.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 20\n- By tool: Read: 6, Edit: 8, Write: 2, Bash: 7, Grep: 3\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx tsc --noEmit` (~50 lines), `npx vitest run --coverage` (~30 lines), `npx vitest run` (~10 lines)\n- Files read: 6 unique, 7 total reads (worktree-manager.test.ts read 2x)\n- Redundant operations: none significant — one re-read of worktree-manager.test.ts to get the conflict detection test pattern after initial partial read"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a818e15894c1b7f45 (use SendMessage with to: 'a818e15894c1b7f45' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 59839\ntool_uses: 40\nduration_ms: 308552</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"74f4684f-cc80-4828-8405-943cba326449","uuid":"30644252-398b-45b7-be7e-3ba41703a98e","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:50:30.981Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/18-2-merge-agent-conflict-resolution.md — implement all tasks, write tests, and mark the story for review. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously through all tasks until complete. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (build failures, test failures, unclear task specs, missing APIs)\n- Workarounds applied (anything hacky, copied patterns that fel