k/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/merge-agent.ts` line 218. Added test covering this case.\n\n2. **MEDIUM — `driver: undefined as never` runtime crash.** `worktree-manager.ts` passed `undefined as never` for the `driver` field and empty strings for descriptions in the `onConflict` callback. Fixed by introducing `MergeConflictInfo` interface that only contains fields `mergeWorktree` can fill (epicId, branch, conflicts, cwd, testCommand). The callback caller is responsible for enriching with driver/descriptions. Changed in `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/worktree-manager.ts`.\n\n3. **MEDIUM — Missing test for all-3-dispatch-failures path.** Added test \"escalates after 3 consecutive dispatch failures\" in `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/merge-agent.test.ts`.\n\n4. **MEDIUM — Catch blocks missing `// IGNORE:` comments.** 4 catch blocks in `merge-agent.ts` violated the project's NFR3 boundary enforcement. Added required comments.\n\n### Coverage Result\n\n- Overall: 96.73% (target: 90%)\n- `merge-agent.ts`: 100% statements\n- All 179 files above 80% per-file floor\n\n---\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: `resolveConflicts` false positive — unparseable test output (0 passed, 0 failed) treated as success. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: `driver: undefined as never` would crash at runtime when merge agent dispatches. Fixed via `MergeConflictInfo` type.\n- MEDIUM: Missing `// IGNORE:` comments on catch blocks fail NFR3 boundary test. Fixed.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- LOW: `buildEscalationMessage` is private (not exported, not directly unit-tested). Only tested indirectly through `resolveConflicts`. Acceptable for now.\n- LOW: `parseTestOutput` is duplicated between `merge-agent.ts` and `worktree-manager.ts`. Should be extracted to a shared utility in a future story.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- Branch coverage for `merge-agent.ts` is 96.15% (line 138 — the `coverage` conditional spread in `parseTestOutput`). Not a real gap, just a branch of conditional object spread.\n- No integration test for the full `mergeWorktree` + `onConflict` + `resolveConflicts` pipeline end-to-end.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The `OnConflictCallback` type now takes `MergeConflictInfo` (partial context) instead of `MergeConflictContext` (full context). The lane-pool caller (Epic 19) must enrich this with `driver`, `mainDescription`, and `branchDescription` before calling `resolveConflicts`. This is a deliberate separation of concerns but creates a coupling point.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 9, Read: 8, Edit: 7, Grep: 2, Write: 0, Skill: 1, Glob: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm run test:coverage` (~80 lines), `npx vitest run merge-agent.test.ts` (~40 lines), `npx vitest run worktree-manager.test.ts` (~50 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none significant — the second `npm run test:coverage` was necessary after fixing boundary violations"}],"totalDurationMs":259331,"totalTokens":73253,"totalToolUseCount":39,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":248,"cache_read_input_tokens":71959,"output_tokens":1045,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":248},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
