{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016JfSxHzHAAo2Ya2CeRQDm4","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 18.2: Merge Agent for Conflict Resolution\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want a merge agent that resolves git conflicts with semantic context,\n11\tso that parallel epics don't require manual conflict resolution.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a new `src/lib/merge-agent.ts` module, **when** imported, **then** it exports a `resolveConflicts(options: MergeConflictContext): Promise<ConflictResolutionResult>` function and the `MergeConflictContext` and `ConflictResolutionResult` interfaces. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n16\t\n17\t2. **Given** `worktree-manager.ts` `mergeWorktree()` returns `MergeResult` with `reason: 'conflict'` and a `conflicts` array, **when** the merge agent is called with the conflicting files, main content, branch content, and both epics' descriptions, **then** the agent receives a prompt containing all conflict context: file paths, `<<<<<<< main` / `>>>>>>> branch` markers, and semantic descriptions of what each epic built. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n18\t\n19\t3. **Given** the merge agent resolves all conflicts in the provided files, **when** resolution completes, **then** the agent writes the resolved content to the conflicting files on disk, stages the changes (`git add`), and commits the merge resolution. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t4. **Given** the merge agent has resolved conflicts and committed, **when** post-resolution validation runs, **then** the full test suite executes on the merged result via `npm test` (or the project's configured test command). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t5. **Given** the test suite fails after agent-resolved merge, **when** failure is detected, **then** the merge is reverted (`git reset --hard HEAD~1`), and the agent retries with additional context including the test failure output (up to 3 total attempts). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t6. **Given** 3 consecutive resolution attempts have all failed (tests fail each time), **when** the third attempt fails, **then** the merge is escalated: the worktree and branch are preserved, and the `ConflictResolutionResult` includes `escalated: true` with `escalationMessage` containing the worktree path, branch name, conflicting files, and a `git diff` command the user can run. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n26\t\n27\t7. **Given** the `ConflictResolutionResult` interface, **when** inspected, **then** it includes: `resolved: boolean`, `attempts: number`, `escalated: boolean`, `escalationMessage?: string`, `testResults?: { passed: number; failed: number; coverage?: number }`, and `resolvedFiles?: string[]`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t8. **Given** the merge agent dispatches a driver (via `AgentDriver.dispatch()`), **when** the driver is invoked, **then** the prompt includes: (a) the list of conflicting files with their full conflict-marker content, (b) a description of what the main branch contains, (c) a description of what the feature branch was building, and (d) instructions to resolve preserving both changes. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n30\t\n31\t9. **Given** the `MergeConflictContext` interface, **when** inspected, **then** it includes: `epicId: string`, `branch: string`, `conflicts: string[]` (file paths), `mainDescription: string`, `branchDescription: string`, `cwd: string`, `testCommand: string`, and `driver: AgentDriver`. <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n32\t\n33\t10. **Given** `worktree-manager.ts` currently aborts the merge on conflict (calls `abortMerge`), **when** the merge agent integration is wired, **then** `mergeWorktree()` gains an optional `onConflict` callback parameter of type `(context: MergeConflictContext) => Promise<ConflictResolutionResult>` that is invoked instead of immediately returning a conflict result. If no callback is provided, behavior is unchanged (returns conflict result as before). <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n36\t\n37\t- [x] Task 1: Define `MergeConflictContext` and `ConflictResolutionResult` interfaces (AC: #1, #7, #9)\n38\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/merge-agent.ts` with both interfaces\n39\t  - [x] `MergeConflictContext`: epicId, branch, conflicts, mainDescription, branchDescription, cwd, testCommand, driver\n40\t  - [x] `ConflictResolutionResult`: resolved, attempts, escalated, escalationMessage?, testResults?, resolvedFiles?\n41\t  - [x] Export the `resolveConflicts` function\n42\t\n43\t- [x] Task 2: Build the conflict context prompt (AC: #2, #8)\n44\t  - [x] Read conflict markers from each file in the `conflicts` array using `readFileSync`\n45\t  - [x] Build a structured prompt with: file path, conflict content, main description, branch description\n46\t  - [x] Include instructions: \"Resolve all conflicts preserving changes from both branches. Both are correct additions.\"\n47\t  - [x] Include instruction to write resolved content to the files and stage + commit\n48\t\n49\t- [x] Task 3: Implement `resolveConflicts()` with retry loop (AC: #3, #4, #5, #6)\n50\t  - [x] Loop up to 3 attempts\n51\t  - [x] Each attempt: dispatch driver with prompt, then run test suite\n52\t  - [x] If tests pass: return `{ resolved: true, attempts, testResults, resolvedFiles }`\n53\t  - [x] If tests fail: revert (`git reset --hard HEAD~1`), retry with test failure context appended to prompt\n54\t  - [x] After 3 failures: return `{ resolved: false, attempts: 3, escalated: true, escalationMessage }` with worktree path, branch, conflicting files, and `git diff` command\n55\t\n56\t- [x] Task 4: Add `onConflict` callback to `mergeWorktree()` (AC: #10)\n57\t  - [x] Add optional `onConflict` parameter to `mergeWorktree` signature\n58\t  - [x] When conflicts detected and `onConflict` is provided: do NOT abort merge, instead call `onConflict` with context\n59\t  - [x] When conflicts detected and `onConflict` is NOT provided: existing behavior (abort, return conflict result)\n60\t  - [x] If `onConflict` returns `resolved: true`, the merge continues with cleanup\n61\t  - [x] If `onConflict` returns `escalated: true`, return a merge failure result preserving worktree\n62\t\n63\t- [x] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#10)\n64\t  - [x] Test: `resolveConflicts` dispatches driver with correct prompt containing conflict markers\n65\t  - [x] Test: successful resolution (tests pass on first attempt) returns `resolved: true, attempts: 1`\n66\t  - [x] Test: resolution with test failure retries up to 3 times with test failure context\n67\t  - [x] Test: after 3 failures, returns `escalated: true` with escalation message containing worktree path, branch, files, git diff command\n68\t  - [x] Test: `ConflictResolutionResult` has correct shape\n69\t  - [x] Test: `MergeConflictContext` has correct shape\n70\t  - [x] Test: `mergeWorktree` with `onConflict` callback invokes callback on conflict\n71\t  - [x] Test: `mergeWorktree` without `onConflict` preserves existing conflict behavior\n72\t  - [x] Test: prompt includes main and branch descriptions\n73\t  - [x] Test: retry prompt includes previous test failure output\n74\t\n75\t## Dev Notes\n76\t\n77\t### Architecture Constraints\n78\t\n79\t- **Architecture Decision 3** (architecture-parallel-execution.md): Merges are serialized — only one `git merge` into main at a time. The merge agent operates INSIDE the merge mutex — the agent resolves conflicts while the mutex is held. Do not release the mutex between conflict detection and resolution.\n80\t- **Merge Agent Boundary** (architecture-parallel-execution.md): The merge agent wraps a driver with merge-specific context. It does NOT know about worktrees or lanes directly — it receives a `MergeConflictContext` with everything it needs. The `cwd` in context points to the main repo (where the conflicted merge is in progress).\n81\t- **Retry Policy**: 3 attempts total. Each failed attempt reverts the merge commit and retries with test failure output appended. After 3 failures, escalate — preserve the worktree and branch for manual resolution.\n82\t- **Driver Dispatch**: Use the `AgentDriver` interface from `src/lib/agents/types.ts`. The merge agent receives a driver instance in its context — it does NOT select the driver itself. The caller (lane pool or engine) is responsible for choosing which driver to use.\n83\t\n84\t### Key Files to Create\n85\t\n86\t| File | Why |\n87\t|------|-----|\n88\t| `src/lib/merge-agent.ts` | New module — conflict resolution dispatch and retry logic |\n89\t| `src/lib/__tests__/merge-agent.test.ts` | Tests for all merge agent functionality |\n90\t\n91\t### Key Files to Modify\n92\t\n93\t| File | Why |\n94\t|------|-----|\n95\t| `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` | Add optional `onConflict` callback to `mergeWorktree()` signature |\n96\t| `src/lib/__tests__/worktree-manager.test.ts` | Add tests for `onConflict` callback behavior |\n97\t\n98\t### Key Files to Read (Do Not Modify)\n99\t\n100\t| File | Why |\n101\t|------|-----|\n102\t| `src/lib/agents/types.ts` | `AgentDriver`, `DispatchOpts`, `OutputContract` — driver dispatch interface |\n103\t| `src/lib/agents/drivers/factory.ts` | `getDriver()` — how to retrieve a registered driver |\n104\t| `src/lib/agents/stream-parser.ts` | `StreamEvent` — events from driver dispatch (consume and ignore during merge) |\n105\t| `src/lib/lane-pool.ts` | `LanePool` — the caller that will wire `onConflict` (not this story's responsibility to wire it) |\n106\t| `src/lib/hierarchical-flow.ts` | `ExecutionConfig` — provides merge_strategy and other config |\n107\t\n108\t### Implementation Patterns\n109\t\n110\t**Prompt construction:**\n111\t```typescript\n112\tfunction buildConflictPrompt(ctx: MergeConflictContext, testFailure?: string): string {\n113\t  const conflictSections = ctx.conflicts.map(file => {\n114\t    const content = readFileSync(join(ctx.cwd, file), 'utf-8');\n115\t    return `### ${file}\\n\\`\\`\\`\\n${content}\\n\\`\\`\\``;\n116\t  }).join('\\n\\n');\n117\t\n118\t  let prompt = `Merge conflict in ${ctx.conflicts.length} file(s) between main and ${ctx.branch}.\\n\\n`;\n119\t  prompt += `**Main branch context:** ${ctx.mainDescription}\\n`;\n120\t  prompt += `**Feature branch context:** ${ctx.branchDescription}\\n\\n`;\n121\t  prompt += `**Conflicting files:**\\n\\n${conflictSections}\\n\\n`;\n122\t  prompt += `Resolve ALL conflicts preserving changes from both branches. Both are correct additions.\\n`;\n123\t  prompt += `Write the resolved content to each file, stage with \\`git add\\`, and commit the merge resolution.\\n`;\n124\t\n125\t  if (testFailure) {\n126\t    prompt += `\\n**Previous attempt failed tests:**\\n\\`\\`\\`\\n${testFailure}\\n\\`\\`\\`\\n`;\n127\t    prompt += `Fix the resolution to make all tests pass.\\n`;\n128\t  }\n129\t  return prompt;\n130\t}\n131\t```\n132\t\n133\t**Retry loop:**\n134\t```typescript\n135\texport async function resolveConflicts(ctx: MergeConflictContext): Promise<ConflictResolutionResult> {\n136\t  const maxAttempts = 3;\n137\t  let lastTestFailure: string | undefined;\n138\t\n139\t  for (let attempt = 1; attempt <= maxAttempts; attempt++) {\n140\t    const prompt = buildConflictPrompt(ctx, lastTestFailure);\n141\t    // Dispatch driver — consume stream events to completion\n142\t    for await (const _event of ctx.driver.dispatch({ prompt, model: '...', cwd: ctx.cwd, sourceAccess: true })) {\n143\t      // Stream events consumed; merge agent doesn't need to display them\n144\t    }\n145\t\n146\t    // Run test suite\n147\t    const testResults = await runTestSuite(ctx.testCommand, ctx.cwd);\n148\t    if (testResults.failed === 0) {\n149\t      return { resolved: true, attempts: attempt, escalated: false, testResults, resolvedFiles: ctx.conflicts };\n150\t    }\n151\t\n152\t    // Revert and retry\n153\t    lastTestFailure = testResults.output;\n154\t    execSync('git reset --hard HEAD~1', { cwd: ctx.cwd });\n155\t  }\n156\t\n157\t  // Escalation after max attempts\n158\t  return {\n159\t    resolved: false,\n160\t    attempts: maxAttempts,\n161\t    escalated: true,\n162\t    escalationMessage: buildEscalationMessage(ctx),\n163\t  };\n164\t}\n165\t```\n166\t\n167\t**onConflict wiring in mergeWorktree (conceptual):**\n168\t```typescript\n169\t// In the catch block where conflicts are detected:\n170\tif (conflicts.length > 0 && onConflict) {\n171\t  // Do NOT abort merge — leave conflicts in place for the agent to resolve\n172\t  const result = await onConflict({ epicId, branch, conflicts, ... });\n173\t  if (result.resolved) {\n174\t    // Agent resolved and committed — run tests is already done inside resolveConflicts\n175\t    this.cleanupWorktree(epicId);\n176\t    return { success: true, testResults: result.testResults, durationMs: Date.now() - start };\n177\t  }\n178\t  // Escalated — abort merge, preserve worktree\n179\t  this.abortMerge(strategy);\n180\t  return { success: false, reason: 'conflict', conflicts, durationMs: Date.now() - start };\n181\t}\n182\t// No callback — existing behavior\n183\tthis.abortMerge(strategy);\n184\treturn { success: false, reason: 'conflict', conflicts, durationMs: Date.now() - start };\n185\t```\n186\t\n187\t### Previous Story (18-1) Intelligence\n188\t\n189\t- Story 18-1 added `mergeWorktree()`, `MergeResult`, `MergeStrategy`, `AsyncMutex`, and `mergeMutex` to `worktree-manager.ts`.\n190\t- The `mergeWorktree` method currently detects conflicts via `detectConflicts()` (checks `git diff --name-only --diff-filter=U`) and aborts immediately, returning `{ success: false, reason: 'conflict', conflicts }`.\n191\t- The `abortMerge(strategy)` method calls `git merge --abort` or `git rebase --abort` depending on strategy.\n192\t- The `runTestSuite(testCommand)` private method uses `execAsync` with timeout, parses pass/fail/coverage from stdout. This pattern should be reused (or extracted) for the merge agent's test validation.\n193\t- The `execGit` private helper wraps `execSync` with 30s timeout and error wrapping.\n194\t- Tests use `vi.mock('node:child_process')` to mock `execSync` and `exec`. Follow the same pattern.\n195\t- The `findBranchForEpic(epicId)` method returns the branch name for a given epicId.\n196\t- 26 merge tests were added in 18-1. The merge agent tests will be in a separate file.\n197\t- Module pattern: TypeScript ESM, `.js` import extensions, vitest.\n198\t\n199\t### Boundary: What This Story Does NOT Include\n200\t\n201\t- **Wiring the onConflict callback into lane-pool or epic-completion** — the lane pool and epic completion flow (Epic 19) will call `mergeWorktree` with the `onConflict` callback. This story adds the callback parameter and the merge agent module; callers are wired later.\n202\t- **TUI merge status display** — Epic 20 will show merge progress, conflict resolution status, and escalation in the TUI.\n203\t- **Telemetry for merge attempts** — not in scope. Telemetry for merge can be added later.\n204\t- **Choosing which driver to use for the merge agent** — the caller passes the driver instance. The merge agent does not contain driver selection logic.\n205\t\n206\t### Edge Cases\n207\t\n208\t- **Conflict in files that don't exist on disk** (e.g., deleted on one side): The `readFileSync` in prompt construction may fail. Handle gracefully — log the file as \"deleted on one side\" in the prompt context.\n209\t- **Agent fails to resolve** (writes incomplete files, doesn't commit): After dispatch completes, check if the working directory is clean. If conflicts remain unresolved (still has conflict markers), treat as failed attempt.\n210\t- **Agent creates new conflicts** (resolves one file but breaks another): The test suite catches this — tests will fail, triggering a retry.\n211\t- **Empty conflict list** (mergeWorktree passes empty array): Guard against this — if `conflicts.length === 0`, return immediately with `resolved: true, attempts: 0`.\n212\t- **Git state corruption during retry** (reset fails): Wrap `git reset --hard HEAD~1` in try/catch. If reset fails, escalate immediately — don't retry on a corrupted state.\n213\t- **Driver dispatch throws** (network error, rate limit): Catch dispatch errors. Treat as a failed attempt — revert and retry. Count toward the 3-attempt limit.\n214\t- **Test command timeout**: The `runTestSuite` already has a timeout. A timeout counts as test failure.\n215\t\n216\t### Project Structure Notes\n217\t\n218\t- Source: TypeScript in `src/`, compiled to `dist/`\n219\t- Tests: vitest, colocated in `src/lib/__tests__/`\n220\t- ESM modules — use `.js` extensions in imports\n221\t- Build: `npm run build`, Test: `npm test`\n222\t- The `merge-agent.ts` should be a focused module (~150-250 lines). Do not bloat with unnecessary abstractions.\n223\t- The `worktree-manager.ts` is ~500 lines after 18-1. Adding the `onConflict` parameter is a small change (~20-30 lines).\n224\t\n225\t### References\n226\t\n227\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-parallel-execution.md#Story 18.2]\n228\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Decision 3 -- Merge Serialization & Agent]\n229\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-parallel-execution.md#Merge Agent Boundary]\n230\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd.md#FR13, FR14, FR16]\n231\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/ux-design-parallel-execution.md#Merge In Progress]\n232\t\n233\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n234\t## Verification Requirements\n235\t\n236\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/18-2-merge-agent-conflict-resolution-proof.md)\n237\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n238\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n239\t\n240\t## Documentation Requirements\n241\t\n242\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n243\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/18-2-merge-agent-conflict-resolution.md\n244\t\n245\t## Testing Requirements\n246\t\n247\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n248\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n249\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n250\t\n251\t## Dev Agent Record\n252\t\n253\t### Agent Model Used\n254\t\n255\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n256\t\n257\t### Debug Log References\n258\t\n259\t### Completion Notes List\n260\t\n261\t### File List\n262\t\n263\t- `src/lib/merge-agent.ts` (created)\n264\t- `src/lib/__tests__/merge-agent.test.ts` (created)\n265\t- `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` (modified — added onConflict callback, OnConflictCallback type)\n266\t- `src/lib/__tests__/worktree-manager.test.ts` (modified — added 5 onConflict tests)\n267\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AAzy1mX2TCPZLWwiowxFDb","session_id":"74f4684f-cc80-4828-8405-943cba326449","uuid":"458a5aa2-865d-432f-8805-8968b04e9e78","timestamp":"2026-04-03T21:56:41.786Z"}
