{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_018Bcg3BDysQ1L4XpxN63B8M","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01SYZY8nXfZXwgZ1eFmWJYDr","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/18-2-merge-agent-conflict-resolution-proof.md","content":"# Story 18-2: Merge Agent for Conflict Resolution — Verification Proof\n\n## Verification Tier: test-provable\n\n## Build & Test Summary\n\n| Check | Result |\n|-------|--------|\n| Build (`npm run build`) | PASS — tsup compiled successfully |\n| Vitest (`npx vitest run`) | PASS — 4919 passed, 0 failed (181 test files) |\n| Lint (`npm run lint`) | FAIL — 8 errors, 58 warnings (pre-existing, unrelated to this story) |\n| Coverage (`npm run test:coverage`) | merge-agent.ts: 100% statements, 100% functions, 100% lines, 96.15% branches |\n| Overall coverage | 97.35% lines |\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Verification\n\n### AC #1: Module exports resolveConflicts, MergeConflictContext, ConflictResolutionResult\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n- File exists: `src/lib/merge-agent.ts`\n- Exports: `export interface MergeConflictContext` (line 26), `export interface ConflictResolutionResult` (line 48), `export async function resolveConflicts(ctx: MergeConflictContext): Promise<ConflictResolutionResult>` (line 177), `export function buildConflictPrompt` (line 75)\n- Test: \"exports resolveConflicts function\" — passed\n\n### AC #2: Merge agent receives prompt with conflict context\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n- Test: \"includes conflict markers from files\" — passed\n- Test: \"dispatches driver with correct prompt containing conflict markers (AC #2, #8)\" — passed\n- Prompt contains file paths, `<<<<<<< main` / `>>>>>>> branch` markers, and semantic descriptions\n\n### AC #3: Agent writes resolved content, stages, and commits\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n- Test: \"returns resolved on first attempt when tests pass\" — passed\n- Prompt includes instruction: `Write the resolved content to each file, stage with \\`git add\\`, and commit the merge resolution.`\n- Resolution delegates file writing/staging/committing to the dispatched driver\n\n### AC #4: Post-resolution test suite validation\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n- Test: \"returns resolved on first attempt when tests pass\" — passed\n- `resolveConflicts` calls `runTestSuite(ctx.testCommand, ctx.cwd)` after each dispatch\n- Tests pass only when `testResults.failed === 0 && testResults.passed > 0`\n\n### AC #5: Revert and retry on test failure with test output context\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n- Test: \"retries up to 3 times with test failure context\" — passed (verified 2 git resets between 3 attempts)\n- Test: \"retry prompt includes previous test failure output\" — passed (second dispatch contains \"Previous attempt failed tests\" and \"TypeError at line 42\")\n- Test: \"includes test failure output on retry (AC #5)\" — passed\n\n### AC #6: Escalation after 3 failed attempts\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n- Test: \"returns escalated after 3 consecutive failures\" — passed (resolved=false, attempts=3, escalated=true)\n- Test: \"escalation message contains worktree path, branch, files, and git diff command\" — passed\n- Escalation message includes: worktree path (`/repo`), branch name, conflicting files, `git diff` command\n\n### AC #7: ConflictResolutionResult interface shape\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n- Interface at line 48 includes: `resolved: boolean`, `attempts: number`, `escalated: boolean`, `escalationMessage?: string`, `testResults?: { passed: number; failed: number; coverage?: number }`, `resolvedFiles?: string[]`\n- Test: \"success result has correct shape\" — passed\n- Test: \"escalated result has correct shape\" — passed\n\n### AC #8: Driver dispatch prompt includes all required context\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n- Test: \"dispatches driver with correct prompt containing conflict markers (AC #2, #8)\" — passed\n- Test: \"includes main and branch descriptions (AC #8)\" — passed\n- Test: \"includes instructions to resolve and commit (AC #8)\" — passed\n- Prompt contains: (a) conflicting files with conflict-marker content, (b) main branch description, (c) feature branch description, (d) instructions to resolve preserving both changes\n\n### AC #9: MergeConflictContext interface shape\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n- Interface at line 26 includes: `epicId: string`, `branch: string`, `conflicts: string[]`, `mainDescription: string`, `branchDescription: string`, `cwd: string`, `testCommand: string`, `driver: AgentDriver`\n- Test: \"has all required fields\" — passed\n\n### AC #10: onConflict callback on mergeWorktree\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n- `OnConflictCallback` type exported from `worktree-manager.ts` (line 129)\n- `mergeWorktree` signature includes `onConflict?: OnConflictCallback` (line 291)\n- Test: \"invokes onConflict callback when conflicts detected and callback provided\" — passed\n- Test: \"does NOT invoke onConflict when no conflicts detected\" — passed\n- Test: \"preserves existing behavior when onConflict is NOT provided\" — passed\n- Test: \"returns conflict result when onConflict returns escalated\" — passed\n- Test: \"passes conflict context to onConflict callback\" — passed\n\n## Test Evidence\n\nAll 30 merge-agent tests passed. All 5 onConflict worktree-manager tests passed.\n\n### merge-agent.test.ts (30 tests)\n\n- MergeConflictContext interface shape (AC #9): 1 test\n- ConflictResolutionResult interface shape (AC #7): 2 tests\n- buildConflictPrompt (AC #2, #8): 6 tests\n- resolveConflicts exports (AC #1): 1 test\n- resolveConflicts empty conflicts guard: 1 test\n- resolveConflicts successful resolution (AC #3, #4): 3 tests\n- resolveConflicts retry on test failure (AC #5): 2 tests\n- resolveConflicts escalation after 3 failures (AC #6): 2 tests\n- resolveConflicts unparseable test output: 1 test\n- resolveConflicts driver dispatch failure: 3 tests\n- resolveConflicts test command failure edge cases: 2 tests\n- resolveConflicts git reset failure during retry: 1 test\n\n### worktree-manager.test.ts (5 onConflict tests)\n\n- invokes onConflict callback when conflicts detected and callback provided\n- does NOT invoke onConflict when no conflicts detected\n- preserves existing behavior when onConflict is NOT provided\n- returns conflict result when onConflict returns escalated\n- passes conflict context to onConflict callback\n\n## Files\n\n| File | Action |\n|------|--------|\n| `src/lib/merge-agent.ts` | Created (252 lines) |\n| `src/lib/__tests__/merge-agent.test.ts` | Created (525 lines) |\n| `src/lib/worktree-manager.ts` | Modified (added OnConflictCallback type, onConflict parameter) |\n| `src/lib/__tests__/worktree-manager.test.ts` | Modified (added 5 onConflict tests) |\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3179,"cache_read_input_tokens":51135,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3179,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AAzy1mX2TCPZLWwiowxFDb","session_id":"74f4684f-cc80-4828-8405-943cba326449","uuid":"12e84b21-da78-4dff-b701-e3bf7c1899a9"}
