{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0185pfDCFuDeec1khfpmeu1v","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 18-2: Merge Agent for Conflict Resolution — Verification Proof\n2\t\n3\t## Verification Tier: test-provable\n4\t\n5\t## Build & Test Summary\n6\t\n7\t| Check | Result |\n8\t|-------|--------|\n9\t| Build (`npm run build`) | PASS — tsup compiled successfully |\n10\t| Vitest (`npx vitest run`) | PASS — 4919 passed, 0 failed (181 test files) |\n11\t| Lint (`npm run lint`) | FAIL — 8 errors, 58 warnings (pre-existing, unrelated to this story) |\n12\t| Coverage (`npm run test:coverage`) | merge-agent.ts: 100% statements, 100% functions, 100% lines, 96.15% branches |\n13\t| Overall coverage | 97.35% lines |\n14\t\n15\t## Acceptance Criteria Verification\n16\t\n17\t### AC #1: Module exports resolveConflicts, MergeConflictContext, ConflictResolutionResult\n18\t\n19\t**Result: PASS**\n20\t\n21\t- File exists: `src/lib/merge-agent.ts`\n22\t- Exports: `export interface MergeConflictContext` (line 26), `export interface ConflictResolutionResult` (line 48), `export async function resolveConflicts(ctx: MergeConflictContext): Promise<ConflictResolutionResult>` (line 177), `export function buildConflictPrompt` (line 75)\n23\t- Test: \"exports resolveConflicts function\" — passed\n24\t\n25\t### AC #2: Merge agent receives prompt with conflict context\n26\t\n27\t**Result: PASS**\n28\t\n29\t- Test: \"includes conflict markers from files\" — passed\n30\t- Test: \"dispatches driver with correct prompt containing conflict markers (AC #2, #8)\" — passed\n31\t- Prompt contains file paths, `<<<<<<< main` / `>>>>>>> branch` markers, and semantic descriptions\n32\t\n33\t### AC #3: Agent writes resolved content, stages, and commits\n34\t\n35\t**Result: PASS**\n36\t\n37\t- Test: \"returns resolved on first attempt when tests pass\" — passed\n38\t- Prompt includes instruction: `Write the resolved content to each file, stage with \\`git add\\`, and commit the merge resolution.`\n39\t- Resolution delegates file writing/staging/committing to the dispatched driver\n40\t\n41\t### AC #4: Post-resolution test suite validation\n42\t\n43\t**Result: PASS**\n44\t\n45\t- Test: \"returns resolved on first attempt when tests pass\" — passed\n46\t- `resolveConflicts` calls `runTestSuite(ctx.testCommand, ctx.cwd)` after each dispatch\n47\t- Tests pass only when `testResults.failed === 0 && testResults.passed > 0`\n48\t\n49\t### AC #5: Revert and retry on test failure with test output context\n50\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"74f4684f-cc80-4828-8405-943cba326449","uuid":"1011382f-9d60-4833-937a-248758d53e56","timestamp":"2026-04-03T22:01:35.603Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/18-2-merge-agent-conflict-resolution-proof.md","content":"# Story 18-2: Merge Agent for Conflict Resolution — Verification Proof\n\n## Verification Tier: test-provable\n\n## Build & Test Summary\n\n| Check | Result |\n|-------|--------|\n| Build (`npm run build`) | PASS — tsup compiled successfully |\n| Vitest (`npx vitest run`) | PASS — 4919 passed, 0 failed (181 test files) |\n| Lint (`npm run lint`) | FAIL — 8 errors, 58 warnings (pre-existing, unrelated to this story) |\n| Coverage (`npm run test:coverage`) | merge-agent.ts: 100% statements, 100% functions, 100% lines, 96.15% branches |\n| Overall coverage | 97.35% lines |\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Verification\n\n### AC #1: Module exports resolveConflicts, MergeConflictContext, ConflictResolutionResult\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n- File exists: `src/lib/merge-agent.ts`\n- Exports: `export interface MergeConflictContext` (line 26), `export interface ConflictResolutionResult` (line 48), `export async function resolveConflicts(ctx: MergeConflictContext): Promise<ConflictResolutionResult>` (line 177), `export function buildConflictPrompt` (line 75)\n- Test: \"exports resolveConflicts function\" — passed\n\n### AC #2: Merge agent receives prompt with conflict context\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n- Test: \"includes conflict markers from files\" — passed\n- Test: \"dispatches driver with correct prompt containing conflict markers (AC #2, #8)\" — passed\n- Prompt contains file paths, `<<<<<<< main` / `>>>>>>> branch` markers, and semantic descriptions\n\n### AC #3: Agent writes resolved content, stages, and commits\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n- Test: \"returns resolved on first attempt when tests pass\" — passed\n- Prompt includes instruction: `Write the resolved content to each file, stage with \\`git add\\`, and commit the merge resolution.`\n- Resolution delegates file writing/staging/committing to the dispatched driver\n\n### AC #4: Post-resolution test suite validation\n\n**Result: PASS**\n\n- Test: \"returns resolved on first attempt when tests pass\" — passed\n- `resolveConflicts` calls `runTestSuite(ctx.testCommand, ctx.cwd)` after each dispatch\n- Tests pass only when `testResults.failed === 0 && testResults.passed > 0`\n\n### AC #5: Revert and retry on test failure with test output context\n","numLines":50,"startLine":1,"totalLines":136}}}
