{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JhEKsCdQ1T9ZWKAVLUgnmC","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 18-2: Merge Agent for Conflict Resolution — Verification Proof\n2\t\n3\t## Verification Tier: test-provable\n4\t\n5\t## Build & Test Summary\n6\t\n7\t| Check | Result |\n8\t|-------|--------|\n9\t| Build (`npm run build`) | PASS — tsup compiled successfully |\n10\t| Vitest (`npx vitest run`) | PASS — 4919 passed, 0 failed (181 test files) |\n11\t| Lint (`npm run lint`) | FAIL — 8 errors, 58 warnings (pre-existing, unrelated to this story) |\n12\t| Coverage (`npm run test:coverage`) | merge-agent.ts: 100% statements, 100% functions, 100% lines, 96.15% branches |\n13\t| Overall coverage | 97.35% lines |\n14\t\n15\t## Acceptance Criteria Verification\n16\t\n17\t### AC #1: Module exports resolveConflicts, MergeConflictContext, ConflictResolutionResult\n18\t\n19\t**Result: PASS**\n20\t\n21\t- File exists: `src/lib/merge-agent.ts`\n22\t- Exports: `export interface MergeConflictContext` (line 26), `export interface ConflictResolutionResult` (line 48), `export async function resolveConflicts(ctx: MergeConflictContext): Promise<ConflictResolutionResult>` (line 177), `export function buildConflictPrompt` (line 75)\n23\t- Test: \"exports resolveConflicts function\" — passed\n24\t\n25\t### AC #2: Merge agent receives prompt with conflict context\n26\t\n27\t**Result: PASS**\n28\t\n29\t- Test: \"includes conflict markers from files\" — passed\n30\t- Test: \"dispatches driver with correct prompt containing conflict markers (AC #2, #8)\" — passed\n31\t- Prompt contains file paths, `<<<<<<< main` / `>>>>>>> branch` markers, and semantic descriptions\n32\t\n33\t### AC #3: Agent writes resolved content, stages, and commits\n34\t\n35\t**Result: PASS**\n36\t\n37\t- Test: \"returns resolved on first attempt when tests pass\" — passed\n38\t- Prompt includes instruction: `Write the resolved content to each file, stage with \\`git add\\`, and commit the merge resolution.`\n39\t- Resolution delegates file writing/staging/committing to the dispatched driver\n40\t\n41\t### AC #4: Post-resolution test suite validation\n42\t\n43\t**Result: PASS**\n44\t\n45\t- Test: \"returns resolved on first attempt when tests pass\" — passed\n46\t- `resolveConflicts` calls `runTestSuite(ctx.testCommand, ctx.cwd)` after each dispatch\n47\t- Tests pass only when `testResults.failed === 0 && testResults.passed > 0`\n48\t\n49\t### AC #5: Revert and retry on test failure with test output context\n50\t\n51\t**Result: PASS**\n52\t\n53\t- Test: \"retries up to 3 times with test failure context\" — passed (verified 2 git resets between 3 attempts)\n54\t- Test: \"retry prompt includes previous test failure output\" — passed (second dispatch contains \"Previous attempt failed tests\" and \"TypeError at line 42\")\n55\t- Test: \"includes test failure output on retry (AC #5)\" — passed\n56\t\n57\t### AC #6: Escalation after 3 failed attempts\n58\t\n59\t**Result: PASS**\n60\t\n61\t- Test: \"returns escalated after 3 consecutive failures\" — passed (resolved=false, attempts=3, escalated=true)\n62\t- Test: \"escalation message contains worktree path, branch, files, and git diff command\" — passed\n63\t- Escalation message includes: worktree path (`/repo`), branch name, conflicting files, `git diff` command\n64\t\n65\t### AC #7: ConflictResolutionResult interface shape\n66\t\n67\t**Result: PASS**\n68\t\n69\t- Interface at line 48 includes: `resolved: boolean`, `attempts: number`, `escalated: boolean`, `escalationMessage?: string`, `testResults?: { passed: number; failed: number; coverage?: number }`, `resolvedFiles?: string[]`\n70\t- Test: \"success result has correct shape\" — passed\n71\t- Test: \"escalated result has correct shape\" — passed\n72\t\n73\t### AC #8: Driver dispatch prompt includes all required context\n74\t\n75\t**Result: PASS**\n76\t\n77\t- Test: \"dispatches driver with correct prompt containing conflict markers (AC #2, #8)\" — passed\n78\t- Test: \"includes main and branch descriptions (AC #8)\" — passed\n79\t- Test: \"includes instructions to resolve and commit (AC #8)\" — passed\n80\t- Prompt contains: (a) conflicting files with conflict-marker content, (b) main branch description, (c) feature branch description, (d) instructions to resolve preserving both changes\n81\t\n82\t### AC #9: MergeConflictContext interface shape\n83\t\n84\t**Result: PASS**\n85\t\n86\t- Interface at line 26 includes: `epicId: string`, `branch: string`, `conflicts: string[]`, `mainDescription: string`, `branchDescription: string`, `cwd: string`, `testCommand: string`, `driver: AgentDriver`\n87\t- Test: \"has all required fields\" — passed\n88\t\n89\t### AC #10: onConflict callback on mergeWorktree\n90\t\n91\t**Result: PASS**\n92\t\n93\t- `OnConflictCallback` type exported from `worktree-manager.ts` (line 129)\n94\t- `mergeWorktree` signature includes `onConflict?: OnConflictCallback` (line 291)\n95\t- Test: \"invokes onConflict callback when conflicts detected and callback provided\" — passed\n96\t- Test: \"does NOT invoke onConflict when no conflicts detected\" — passed\n97\t- Test: \"preserves existing behavior when onConflict is NOT provided\" — passed\n98\t- Test: \"returns conflict result when onConflict returns escalated\" — passed\n99\t- Test: \"passes conflict context to onConflict callback\" — passed\n100\t\n101\t## Test Evidence\n102\t\n103\tAll 30 merge-agent tests passed. All 5 onConflict worktree-manager tests passed.\n104\t\n105\t### merge-agent.test.ts (30 tests)\n106\t\n107\t- MergeConflictContext interface shape (AC #9): 1 test\n108\t- ConflictResolutionResult interface shape (AC #7): 2 tests\n109\t- buildConflictPrompt (AC #2, #8): 6 tests\n110\t- resolveConflicts exports (AC #1): 1 test\n111\t- resolveConflicts empty conflicts guard: 1 test\n112\t- resolveConflicts successful resolution (AC #3, #4): 3 tests\n113\t- resolveConflicts retry on test failure (AC #5): 2 tests\n114\t- resolveConflicts